OL,3,CCoroner calls for better water safety
OL,4,Ceducation after beach drownings
OL,6,FDuring the inquest into their deaths,
OL,7,Fthe parents of the two had questioned
OL,8,Fthe lifeguard response to the incident
OL,9,Fand whether better signs should have
OL,10,Fbeen in place warning of the risk of
OL,11,Frip currents by the pier, as well as
OL,12,Fproviding safety advice for swimmers.
OL,14,FDorset senior coroner Rachael Griffin
OL,15,Fruled that the deaths were accidental
OL,16,Fand said that she was satisfied
OL,17,F"nothing more than was done, could
OL,18,Fhave been done" to prevent the tragic
OL,19,Fdeaths of the children.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
